<DOC><DOCNO> AP901102-0254 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-11-02-90 1739EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-FordRecall     11-02 0126</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Ford Recall,0121</SECOND><HEAD>Ford Increases Number of Possible Defective Air Bags</HEAD><DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ford Motor Co. said Friday up to 3,0001990 and 1991 model cars may have defective air bags, up from itsoriginal estimate of 133.   Earlier this week, Ford announced a recall of 55,000 cars tolocate and replace the defective bags. That number stands, Fordspokesman Jim Trainor said.   The No. 2 automaker's module supplier, TRW Vehicle SafetySystems Inc., further reviewed production records and informed Fordof the increase in the possible number of cars with defective bags,Trainor said.   Ford is recalling 1990 models Taurus, Sable, Continental, Tempoand Topaz and 1990-1991 Crown Victoria and Grand Marquis models.</TEXT></DOC>